Privacy Policy
Effective Date: [7.03.2026]

Focus Watch ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our mobile application.

1. Information Collection and Use
To provide a better experience while using our Service, we may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information. The information that we request will be retained by us and used as described in this privacy policy.
  1.1 Special Permissions & App Functionality:
To provide our core "Focus Mode" and "App Blocking" features, our application requires the following specific permissions:

App Usage Stats (PACKAGE_USAGE_STATS): This permission is used solely to detect which app is currently in the foreground. This allows Focus Watch to block distracting apps during your focus sessions. We do not collect, store, or transmit any data regarding your overall app usage history.

System Alert Window: This is used to display the "Focus Overlay" screen on top of other applications when they are blocked, ensuring you stay committed to your tasks.

Notifications (POST_NOTIFICATIONS): Used to send you reminders for your habits, daily missions, and focus session updates.

Vibrate & Wake Lock: These are used to provide haptic feedback during interactions and to prevent the device from sleeping during an active focus timer.

2. Third-Party Services
Our app uses third-party services that may collect information used to identify you. Below are the providers we use:

Google Play Services: Used for app functionality and security.

Google AdMob & AdSense: Used to deliver personalized and non-personalized advertisements. They may use tracking technologies to serve ads based on your interests.

Firebase & Google Analytics: We use these to understand app usage, track crashes, and improve user experience. These services collect data such as device identifiers, session information, and usage patterns.

3. Log Data
In case of an error in the app, we collect data and information (through third-party products) on your phone called Log Data. This may include information such as your device Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, device name, operating system version, the configuration of the app when utilizing our Service, and other statistics.

4. Cookies and Tracking
The app does not use “cookies” explicitly. However, the app may use third-party code and libraries (like AdMob) that use “cookies” or mobile identifiers to collect information and improve their services.

5. Children’s Privacy
Our services do not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13 years of age. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we immediately delete this from our servers.

6. Data Security
We value your trust in providing us your Personal Information, thus we are striving to use commercially acceptable means of protecting it. But remember that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes.

8. Contact Us
